<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/1041: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-07T18:00:00-05:00">May 7, 1937—6
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>24. The President and the Minister for Foreign Affairs continue
                                inquiry as to the Department’s reaction vis-à-vis the memorandum
                                submitted with my despatch 748, April 17.<note n="6" xml:id="d32fn6">Not printed; memoranda submitted with this despatch covered
                                    conversations reported in telegram No. 22, April 17, 7 p.m.,
                                        <ref target="#pg_46">p. 46</ref>.</note> When may I expect
                                instructions in the premises?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzalez</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>